	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001093_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'--> 
<!--Hand 01 16 top left--><!--hand 02 67464 top right-->
<lb/><p rend="right">Hamilton</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">14<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi><choice><abbr>Sept<hi rend="sup">r</hi></abbr><expan>September</expan></choice></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1857</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">rs</hi></hi> Cowan</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I lately wrote 
<lb/>to <persName>Sir William 
<lb/>Johnston</persName> fixing 
<lb/>Monday the 
<lb/>21<hi rend="sup">st</hi> as convenient 
<lb/>for the meeting 
<lb/>at Edinburgh 
<lb/>I did not expect 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001093_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'--> 
<lb/>any answer to 
<lb/>that unless 
<lb/>the following 
<lb/>day should be 
<lb/>more convenient 
<lb/>I now beg 
<lb/>to trouble you 
<lb/>for a single 
<lb/>line to say 
<lb/>at what hour 
<lb/>on that day I am 
<lb/>expected. My 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001093_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'--> 
<lb/>friends wish 
<lb/>to keep me 
<lb/>over Sunday 
<lb/>if possible. If 
<lb/>I leave Glasgow 
<lb/>at 9. or 10 <add place="above" resp="#CO">A.M.</add> shall 
<lb/>I be in time? 
<lb/>Please address</p>
<lb/><p><placeName>4 Athol Place</placeName></p>
<lb/><p>Glasgow</p>
<lb/><p>&amp; excuse my 
<lb/>troubling you thus</p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001093_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'-->
<lb/><p>I am &amp;c</p>
<lb/><p>David Livingstone</p>
<lb/><p>Perhaps <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Cowan</persName>
<lb/>may be back 
<lb/>by that time 
<lb/>&amp; I shall have 
<lb/>the pleasure 
<lb/>of meeting him 
<lb/>too</p>
			
